pullRequest.body:
* Prove some properties of `PiTensorProduct.map`, for example the compatibility with composition and reindeixing, and the fact that it sends the identity to the identity. 
* Construct `PiTensorProduct.map` as a `MultilinearMap` on the family of linear maps.
* Upgrade `PiTensorProduct.map f` to a linear equivalence called `PiTensorProduct.congr f` when `f` is a family of linear equivalences. 
* For `ι` a `Fintype`, define the canonical linear equivalence (given by multiplication) `constantBaseRingEquiv`  from `⨂ i : ι, R` and `R`.

I think slightly cleaner to use `Set.range` here
```suggestion
theorem span_tprod_eq_top :
    Submodule.span R (Set.range (tprod R)) = (⊤ : Submodule R (⨂[R] i, s i)) :=
```

nit: if you wrap the statement, you should wrap after the first `:` too:
```suggestion
theorem map_range_eq_span_tprod :
    LinearMap.range (map f) =
      Submodule.span R { t | ∃ (m : (i : ι) → s i), tprod R (fun i ↦ f i (m i)) = t } := by
```
I'm not convinced this is necessarily worth giving a name, but another reviewer can tie-break
I only gave it a name because of the existence of  [`TensorProduct.mapIncl`](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/TensorProduct.html#TensorProduct.mapIncl).
Ah, that's a good enough reason; can you reference that in the docstring?
Done.
Can you use `\comp\_l` notation here?
Done.

```suggestion
    map (fun i ↦ f₁ i * f₂ i) = map f₁ * map f₂ :=
```
Done.
This can proved in one line if you show that `map` is a `RingHom`

Okay, but then we should also prove the corresponding result for [`TensorProduct.map`](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/TensorProduct.html#TensorProduct.map), to get a shorter proof of [`TensorProduct.map_pow`](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/TensorProduct.html#TensorProduct.map_pow).

Wait, now that the coffee kicked in, I have to ask: a `RingHom` from what to what ? Since `map` is multilinear in the `f i`, the only possibility I see is to prove that the lift of `mapMultilinear` is a `RingHom` from `⨂[R] i, (s i →ₗ[R] s i)` to `(⨂[R] i, s i) →ₗ[R] (⨂[R] i, s i)`, but I don't know if that's what you meant.
I think I must have meant a MonoidHom
Like so ? I now question whether we should have `map_pow` at all, since the proof is literally `MonoidHom.map_pow`.
Indeed the linter is complaining that `map_pow` can now be proved by `simp`, and I agree with it for once.

```suggestion
    MultilinearMap R (fun (i : ι) ↦ s i →ₗ[R] t i) ((⨂[R] i, s i) →ₗ[R] ⨂[R] i, t i) where
```

```suggestion
@[simps]
noncomputable def mapMultilinear :
```
then you can drop the lemma below.

```suggestion
`⨂[R] i, s' i` are linearly equivalent.

This is the n-ary version of `TensorProduct.congr`
```

```suggestion
    map (f ^ n) = map f ^ n := MonoidHom.map_pow mapMonoidHom _ _
```
is how you appease the linter

```suggestion
  exact apply_update (fun i F => F (x i)) f i u j
```

For consistency, I'd encourage you to use
```suggestion
      Submodule.span R { t | ∃ (m : Π i, s i), tprod R (fun i ↦ f i (m i)) = t } := by
```
everywhere that you're changing this file
I wanted to before... Okay, I think I found them all this time. (I searched on `→`.)
I think these should be `map_update_add` etc

Here's my logic behind the naming: `PiTensorProduct.map` is a `MultilinearMap` (in fact, we are in the process of proving it), and these lemmas `map_add` and `map_smul` are proving the same things as `MultilinearMap.map_add` and `MultilinearMap.map_smul`. So they should have the same names.
I guess I don't care that much, so am happy to go with that argument. I agree it's consistent.

Another good lemma to have is
```lean
map_comp_reindex_symm : map f ∘ₗ (reindex R s e).symm = (reindex R t e).symm ∘ₗ map (fun i => f (e.symm i))
```
Ok, I added the lemma.
To match `TensorProduct`, can you rename this to `map_comp_reindex`, and remove the `apply` from the other lemma?
To match `TensorProduct`, it should even be `map_comp_reindex_eq`, I believe.
I think this belongs in `RingTheory/PiTensorProduct`, as I believe it is an `AlgEquiv` with no stronger assumptions
I have a version of this; I'll split it off to its own PR
Should I take your :+1: as an agreement that the code there replaces this? If so, can you delete this, and then I'll merge the rest of this PR.
Yes, I went to look at your PR, it looked good to me and I didn't see anything I'd want to change in it. I deleted the definition and lemma from this PR.
It's not clear to me that `simp` is appropriate here, especially as you didn't put it on `map_reindex`. Was there a particular argument you had in mind for doing so?

No, I originally put it on buth, then deleted it on `map_reindex` when I noticed it wasn't on `TensorProduct.map_comm`. Of course, there's a very good reason it's not a `TensorProduct.map_comm` and it doesn't apply here, but anyway I'll just go delete the second `simp`.

```suggestion
@[simps]
def mapMonoidHom : (Π i, s i →ₗ[R] s i) →* ((⨂[R] i, s i) →ₗ[R] ⨂[R] i, s i) where
```
If you make these `protected`, then you don't need to adjust the proofs in the last three files in this PR.
Thanks, that's a useful trick ! Now the changes are all in one file.
